46c62593d754dae0592917fca33b115f1a0f0efd46d461dbb4b85","event_uuid":"6d551576-0389-49e8-aeef-8610260d19c6","position":{"commit_sha":"bee5f2186eac9839da5ab8b5a0ec4d8cd2f7641a","position":"1784444354304769001-6d551576-0389-49e8-aeef-8610260d19c6"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"e1840873baa5f77cc8ab770f53b06a9187db018f9aa6290fce1bf20e3e5c46ac","event_uuid":"d0a3bd31-9e2f-4b85-8289-7002a599f3d0","position":{"commit_sha":"bee5f2186eac9839da5ab8b5a0ec4d8cd2f7641a","position":"1784444354544835001-d0a3bd31-9e2f-4b85-8289-7002a599f3d0"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"e00bd9b7886fa866a07facb8d7b0d272b7eab5f4aa53c773137437021dcb7902","event_uuid":"0b34f142-cdd2-4688-9594-b688e9ebbac9","position":{"commit_sha":"1cf6bb3550758f9009d1e4f4d752df985938d57e","position":"1784444611307108244-0b34f142-cdd2-4688-9594-b688e9ebbac9"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-214_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"6e3fbad8-702f-4987-ad70-cc88122eea43","comments":[],"created_at":1784416834043440001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[{"link_uuid":"2a0dcc24-7c5f-4b80-b7ff-ef93a31458ed","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"ed13-e224-1ece-44ff"}],"description":"## What\nOne-time backfill of `close_class` for already-closed bugs that lack it, inferred from STRUCTURAL signals only (no prose recovery, no LLM guessing): a bug whose reduced `reverts` contains a revert of a STATUS/COMMITS event → `regression`; a bug with a plan-review `BLOCK` in its `REVIEW_RESULT` history → `plan_defect`; a bug with a `gate_error_v1` ERROR on its sidecar streams → `env_integration`; otherwise → `undetermined`. Every backfilled value is labeled and segregated from authoritative going-forward `--class` values.\n\n## Data-access ground truth (the plan is built on this)\n- **Only backfill bugs where `state[\"close_class\"]` is ABSENT** (a bug already closed with `--class` keeps its authoritative value; `close_class` is folded on the `*→closed` edge, `_processors.py:195-209`). Reduce via `reduce_ticket`.\n- **REVERT signal**: reduced `state[\"reverts\"]` is a list of `{target_event_uuid, target_event_type, timestamp, ...}` (`_processors.py:452-462`) — a revert of a SPECIFIC prior event of ANY type. A \"regression\" inference requires a revert whose `target_event_type` is `STATUS` or `COMMITS` (a substantive revert), not a revert of a COMMENT/LINK.\n- **plan-review BLOCK signal**: `REVIEW_RESULT` events are reducer-ignored (`_version.py:77`) and NOT in compiled state — read them via `rebar.llm.plan_review.sidecar.all_review_results(id, repo_root=)` (returns retained payloads; check `verdict==\"BLOCK\"`). (Retention caps at 50/ticket, so a very old BLOCK may be pruned — an accepted best-effort limit, logged.)\n- **env_integration signal**: a `gate_error_v1` ERROR record on the bug's `REVIEW_RESULT`/`COMPLETION_VERDICT` streams. This MUST use a **raw event-file scan** (NOT `all_review_results`, whose schema guard accepts only `plan_review_result_v1/v2` and silently skips `gate_error_v1`): resolve the ticket dir (`tracker_dir`+`resolve_ticket_dir_name`), glob `*-REVIEW_RESULT.json` AND `*-COMPLETION_VERDICT.json`, `json.load` each, and check `event[\"data\"].get(\"schema\") == \"gate_error_v1\"` — mirroring the `scan_event_payloads` helper in `tests/unit/workflow/test_gate_error_sidecar.py`. (The plan-review BLOCK signal above CAN use `all_review_results` since a BLOCK is a `plan_review_result_v2` payload; only the gate_error scan needs the raw path.)\n- These signals are **heuristic evidence, not proof**: the structural facts (a REVERT of a STATUS event; a BLOCK verdict; an ERROR record) are reliable, but the class they imply is an inference. Anything not confidently inferable → `undetermined` (the explicit escape bucket in `CLOSE_CLASSES`).\n\n## The backfill artifact (concrete target + idempotency)\nBackfilled classifications are written as one JSON object per line to a dedicated, git-TRACKED NDJSON file **`.rebar/backfill-close-class.ndjson`** — a *separate* artifact from the authoritative STATUS-folded `close_class`, so backfilled values are never confused with (or aggregated into) authoritative ones. Because `.gitignore` blanket-ignores `.rebar/*` (line 20) with per-file negations, the script's Files list includes a `.gitignore` edit adding `!.rebar/backfill-close-class.ndjson` (mirroring `!.rebar/criteria_routing.json`) so the artifact persists.\n- **Record shape:** `{\"ticket_id\", \"close_class\", \"source\": \"backfill_classified\", \"confidence\": \"classified\", \"evidence\": \"<which signal fired>\", \"ts\": \"<ISO-8601>\"}`.\n- **Idempotency (precise mechanism):** the script first reads the existing artifact and builds the set of already-recorded `ticket_id`s; it SKIPS any bug already present in that set AND any bug whose reduced `state[\"close_class\"]` is set (authoritative). So re-running appends nothing new for already-processed bugs — idempotent by `ticket_id`. `--dry-run` prints the classifications without writing.\n\n## Files\n- `scripts/backfill_bug_class.py` — new standalone script (per the above): classify closed bugs lacking `close_class`, append labeled records to `.rebar/backfill-close-class.ndjson`, idempotent by `ticket_id`, `--dry-run` supported.\n- `.gitignore` — add `!.rebar/backfill-close-class.ndjson` (past the blanket `.rebar/*` ignore) so the artifact is tracked.\n- `tests/scripts/test_backfill_bug_class.py` — new (tier `tests/scripts/`, `pytestmark = pytest.mark.scripts` — NOT the nonexistent `tests/unit/scripts/`).\n\n## Approach\nThe original free-text reasons were discarded, so only structural signals are trustworthy. Classifying solely from REVERT / plan-review BLOCK / gate ERROR linkage (and `undetermined` for everything else) keeps the backfill honest and avoids contamination. Every backfilled record carries `source=backfill_classified, confidence=classified` so the c085 registry keeps them apart from authoritative structural series (`is_authoritative(\"backfill_classified\")` is False).\n\n## Tests\n- Unit (`tests/scripts/`, real temp store; craft closed bugs with the signals): a bug with a REVERT of a STATUS event → `regression`; a bug with a `REVIEW_RESULT` BLOCK → `plan_defect`; a bug with a `gate_error_v1` ERROR → `env_integration`; a plain closed bug with none → `undetermined`; a bug already carrying `close_class` is SKIPPED (not re-backfilled). Every emitted record carries `source=backfill_classified` + `confidence=classified`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `tests/scripts/test_backfill_bug_class.py` passes (tier `scripts`): the four fixtures classify to `regression`, `plan_defect`, `env_integration`, `undetermined` respectively (exact-value asserts on the emitted record's `close_class`).\n- [ ] a bug that already has `state[\"close_class\"]` is NOT overwritten/re-emitted (idempotence + authoritative-value protection) — asserted.\n- [ ] every backfilled record carries `source==\"backfill_classified\"` and `confidence==\"classified\"`, and `is_authoritative(record.source)` is False — asserted on the output, proving segregation from authoritative series.\n- [ ] a REVERT whose only `target_event_type` is `COMMENT` does NOT yield `regression` (it falls through to `undetermined`) — asserted, proving the substantive-revert filter.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"scripts/backfill_bug_class.py","reason":"backfill script"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["depends_on","ed13-e224-1ece-44ff"],["parent","86ac-086a-20ad-4327"]],"parent_id":"86ac-086a-20ad-4327","parent_status_uuid":"6d551576-0389-49e8-aeef-8610260d19c6","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["metrics","backfill"],"ticket_id":"5062-30a8-9153-4c61","ticket_type":"task","title":"Backfill historical bug --class from structural signals only","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["1ef15c73-c913-4949-ab64-27150f451c8b","b0fc14d4-c64f-43ca-a6a1-ef61ed8e26cf","2a0dcc24-7c5f-4b80-b7ff-ef93a31458ed","b690bd37-630e-425e-9ceb-bcae0194b1cb","77886386-b513-4c42-b1b7-2268703d93da","a8e441ee-c9c4-4b75-83ae-ad81e0b60bed","247842eb-e18c-451a-b4af-565903073ce6","5a6535d0-2fd1-4530-bc99-6381dd8ee0f6","6d551576-0389-49e8-aeef-8610260d19c6","d0a3bd31-9e2f-4b85-8289-7002a599f3d0","0b34f142-cdd2-4688-9594-b688e9ebbac9"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784444611307108245,"uuid":"bcb548a3-9574-4a90-ae6b-701f013cabef"}